        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>38, Queen’s Gardens, | Bayswater.</placeName>
                    <date>July. 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1875</date>
                    <salute>Dear Darwin,</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I was surprised by your new volume—wondering how, with your state of health, you had managed to make such extensive inquiries and to prepare so elaborate a statement of results. Thank you very much for it.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I would it had come years ago, while the <hi rend="underline">Biology</hi> was in progress;<ref target="#foot.f2"/> so that I might have turned its varied information to more account than I fear I shall now be able to do</p>
<p>Sincerely yours | Herbert Spencer</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Spencer’s name is on CD’s presentation list for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_4097.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Insectivorous plants</hi></ref> (Appendix IV).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><hi rend="italic">Principles of biology</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_7369.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Spencer 1864–7</ref>).</note>
        </div>        
            
